    "d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_DLntwV": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What makes a rubber or silicone squeegee better than a regular plastic squeegee?",
            "content": "<p>Rubber and silicone squeegees are far more effective than traditional plastic ones because they create better contact with the surface, allowing water, soap and residue to be removed more efficiently in a single pass. They will not scratch floors or furniture, and are also more durable and long-lasting.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_nkCiz9": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is a silicone squeegee used for?",
            "content": "<p>A silicone squeegee is used to remove water, soap, and residue from smooth surfaces like floors, windows, mirrors, shower screens, tiles, decks and awnings. It leaves a streak-free finish with minimal effort.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_ATRXDy": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I use a silicone squeegee on all surfaces?",
            "content": "<p>Silicone squeegees are ideal for smooth, non-porous surfaces such as floors, glass, roofs, tiles, mirrors, awnings, solar panels, and polished metal. </p>"
          }
        },
        "item_ikMTTN": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How do I clean and maintain a silicone squeegee?",
            "content": "<p>Simply rinse the blade with warm water after use to remove soap and residue. Silicone is naturally resistant to mould and build-up, making it very low maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_JiUKf8": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What makes silicone squeegees good for caravans and travel?",
            "content": "<p>Silicone squeegees are lightweight, durable, and compact—perfect for caravans and travel. They help quickly remove condensation, water spots, and grime from windows, shower areas, screens, awnings and solar panels while on the road. Our squeegees are fitted with a collapsible 4-part handle for easy storage.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_gbaLKR": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is a silicone squeegee better than a plastic one?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. Silicone squeegees are more flexible than plastic, allowing them to maintain better contact with the surface. This results in a more effective clean, fewer streaks, and less skipping or scratching. They are also a much more durable option than traditional plastic ones.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_6rFt8d": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between the rubber and silicone squeegees?",
            "content": "<p>Not all that much - some would say that  rubber is a bit firmer for tougher cleaning, while silicone is somewhat softer for lighter, everyday<strong> </strong>use. Both are highly durable, easy to clean with water and very effective.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_XdrFyG": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Where is our warehouse located?",
            "content": "<p>Our warehouse is located in Cheltenham, Melbourne. </p>"
          }
        },
        "template--19202935587090__d9e91537-6225-4b57-bd84-e5d10e8558b3-1686662624baccc985-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do BrightTools Squeegees come with a warranty?",
            "content": "<p>Absolutely! We stand behind the quality of our squeegees. Each one is backed by a 2 year <a href=\"/pages/warranty\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Warranty\">warranty</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "dc709b98-8f74-4f10-9911-a3d0da4bdcf4": {
          "type": "item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "I have a question that is not listed here. How can I get in touch with BrightTools?",
            "content": "<p>No problem at all! We're here to help. If you have any additional questions or need further assistance, simply visit our <a href=\"/pages/contact\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Contact\">contact page.</a></p>"
          }
        }
      },
